gomodel:SYNGO_1704  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: The authors use light microscopy to localize dynamin in mouse photoreceptor cells. The protein is found in the synaptic layers of the retina in close proximity to the synaptic ribbon, the release site in these neurons. Figure 2 uses standard confocal microscopy. Figure 4 uses immunogold electron microscopy to localize dynamin at the synaptic plasma membrane in proximity to the synaptic ribbon.\n\n15/11/2017 Pim\n- For PMID:23785143 I allow annotation to term 'presynaptic endocytic zone' because the authors claim this as an experimental finding. The title states \"A local, periactive zone endocytic machinery at photoreceptor synapses in close vicinity to synaptic ribbons\". Experimental description: From legend to figure 2, \"Distribution of dynamin in photoreceptor ribbon synapses.....thin sections of the mouse retina\"." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7806-5662" ;
        dc:date           "2017-11-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1704" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

